{"id":"1202.0112","submitter":"Yuehong Feng","authors":"Shu Wang, Yuehong Feng and Xin Li","title":"The asymptotic behavior of globally smooth solutions of bipolar\n  non-isentropic compressible Euler-Maxwell system for plasma","comments":"27pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1142/S0218202514500390","report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The bipolar non-isentropic compressible Euler-Maxwell system is investigated\nin $R^3$ in the present paper, and the $L^q$ time decay rate for the global\nsmooth solution is established. It is shown that the total densities, total\ntemperatures and magnetic field of two carriers converge to the equilibrium\nstates at the same rate $(1+t)^{-3/2+3q/2}$ in $L^q$ norm. But, both the\ndifference of densities and the difference of temperatures of two carriers\ndecay at the rate $(1+t)^{-2-\\frac{1}{q}}$, and the velocity and electric field\ndecay at the rate $(1+t)^{-3/2+\\frac{1}{2q}}$. This phenomenon on the charge\ntransport shows the essential difference between the non-isentropic unipolar\nEuler-Maxwell and the bipolar isentropic Euler-Maxwell system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2012 08:17:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Feb 2012 13:01:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 26 Feb 2012 23:37:50 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 28 Feb 2012 23:43:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-16"}
