 to recognize\nsources, which may require that source finding algorithms effectively work with\nmulti-resolution and multi-wavelength data. The work underscores the importance\nof using source lists-as opposed to component lists-and correcting for the\nnoise bias in order to precisely estimate counts close to the image noise and\ndetermine the upturn at sub-mJy flux density.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2012 10:09:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 11 Sep 2012 13:28:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
